Bluetongue, Bosnia and Herzegovina
--------------------------------------
Information received on 19 Sep 2014 from Dr Ljubomir Kalaba, Director, Veterinary Office, Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Relations, Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 30 Apr 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 30 Apr 2014
Report date: 19 Sep 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 19 Sep 2014
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: September 2003
Manifestation of disease: Sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: Not typed
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to the whole country
New outbreaks (1)

Outbreak 1: Quarantine, GRADISKA
Date of start of the outbreak: 30 Apr 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 150 / 3 / - / - / -

Affected population: Bluetongue has been serologically detected during quarantine of cattle imported from Germany which are not vaccinated against bluetongue, and without clinical signs.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 150 / 3 / - / - / -

